snippet.textDisplay: 22 years old and recent fan of Ozzy i always liked black sabbath and metal even when i was in high school and pretending to like hip hop. ozzy has mean so much to me and i can never forget him, and for the rest of my life ill be turning people on to him. im no man of faith, i find it hard to have any faith at all really, my dad passed at 55 and at his funeral a bat came by in day time landed right beside me passed all the other people, bats are usually timid and stay way from people and sick or not they usually dont come out in the middle of the day. i was just starting to accept that i love metal and was exploring the genre, ozzy (All of his work) spoke to me,his lyrics,his mission to be the best rock and roll singer even tho he wasnt a perfect vocalist. his problem with drug abuse. its inspiring, HE IS TRULY INSPIRING. back to my father, i feel like the bat was the only way to let me know, a secular person, that he was okay, whatever that may mean. and in his last cognitive moments i was talking about my recent devotion to music and said im a rocker just like you, he chcuckled. when ever my dad would play a harder song than gnr, my mom always said "i just cant do that music i was never a 'rocker" in air quotes. me rolling my eyes everytime, but still i took those air quotes to heart my mom skewed me off of it. and so i think that phrase im a rocker just liek you meant more than face value. i hope he remembered or thought about that in his last moments. im sorry i cant proof read this, spent too much time here already

snippet.textDisplay: I don't know why I am even writing this because Ozzy is never going to read it. Even as heartfelt as this is going to be he will miss it.  Ozzy you are a one in a million man. You will NEVER be anything but the fabulously special man that you are.  You have so much talent and love and personality that you can never be ordinary. You have a voice that makes the average person cry about.  You have so much love for your family that no ordinary man could ever have.  You love those precious little dogs so much that I only want to see more of you interacting with them and how much they love you.  You have talent that is greater than hundreds of bands of men all  put together.   You are just about worshipped by the whole world.  And this is because you are so special!!!!   You will never be an ordinary man. You can't be because of all that you have done for this world, the memories that you have given people that have had the privilege of either seeing you or meeting you will change their lives forever.  It would change mine if I ever got to meet you and your wife and kids.  I am so proud of Kelly and Jack.  I always worried  about how they would grow up and be able to do honorable things for you and your wife.  And you know what?  Those two and I say those two because I don't know of the third child. But those two have grown and have turned into two of the most fabulous adults. I am so proud of who they have become and who they are in their lives today. They are a product of a couple who have loved and taught them how to be good people and they are.  Ozzy!!!  You are a man that I LOVE  but not in a romantic way.  You belong to Sharon the most beautiful woman there is. I LOVE you because you are NOT an ordinary man and for who you have become over the many years of going places you were unsure of.  You are NOT an ordinary man because the world loves you too and you have to fight and keep on going. Keep that wonderful smile on your face and try not to get too down with things.  Everything will turn out how it is supposed to and try and remember this.  No matter what .... the best days of ever are in front of you. Just wait and see.  Take care of yourself. I love you Ozzy.  Barbara  I have to add one more thing... This video made me shed tears of pride for you and all of your accomplishments. So don't think  about ordinary!!!!
